Our Company

Our mission is to create a true and equal opportunity employment culture.

Our goal is to promote an inclusive workplace of professional diversity within all organizations.

Our MPower platform provides an affordable, comprehensive, member-centric approach to transform employment opportunities for individuals.

*M2N uses the term minority to include any individual who identifies as something other than the white male majority.  We have not yet determined the perfect term that accurately encompasses both unique individual identities while providing a sense of belonging within groups of people. Our aim is to provide an inclusive experience for all members by allowing every individual to identify themselves as they prefer without creating additional constraints or labels.

Eric Stanley
FOUNDER & CEO

Robert Eric Stanley is an accomplished Black business professional with extensive experience in the pharmaceutical, insurance and technology industries.  He built a successful career through continuing education, empowerment of his ethnicity, and executive mentorship.

Over the last few years initiatives to increase diversity and inclusion in the workplace have increased, however, the results of these efforts have been underwhelming.

The failure of these programs, coupled with Eric’s desire to leverage his lived experience, serves as the inspiration for creating M2N, the Minority Moves Network, and the MPower platform.

Shaun Hawkins
ADVISORY BOARD
Paul Lockhart
ADVISORY BOARD
Kathy Jordan
ADVISORY BOARD

Shaun is the founder of the ProSyte Companies, a diversified holding entity investing in businesses and real estate in the US and Europe. Hawkins was the Chief Diversity Officer for Eli Lilly & Co.

Paul is a seasoned executive recognized for his ability to grow high-performing organizations by rapidly scaling revenue operations in both start-up and turn- around engagements.

Kathy is the CEO of KJordan Consulting, a strategic coaching firm which works with entertainers and professional athletes to maximize their personal, professional, and business performance.
